Database
========
From VLSI database:
131.dat: 131 points
237.dat: 237 points
343.dat: 343 points

Usage
=====
1. Compilation:
---------------
$ g++ Evolutionary.cpp -o Evolutionary
$ javac Visualization.java 

* Note: in the console, the users can choose another data file name or other parameters.
2. Run :
--------
$ ./Evolutionary
Data file: 131.dat
Number of iterations (default 100): 100
Population size (default 1000): 1000
Selection percent (default 30): 30

Iteration 0
...
Iteration 99
Best gene: 569.479

Iteration 100
Best gene: 569.479

Saved the best current solution to file solution.dat

Best solution found by Evolutionary Algorithm: 569.479

3. Visualization (the output file from last step is solution.dat):
------------------------------------------------------------------
$ java Visualization
Data file contains points' coordinates: 131.dat
Solution file: solution.dat

Image solution.png will be generated.
